reviews.review_text:
Fire to open the 2nd ? Wow! I am not sure how many times they opened a second set with Fire, but it is kind of interesting little change. 

Not the best ever but certainly nice and well played.

Sound quality is good.I am most definetly getting it for the novelty of Fire opening up 2nd. THere is also some other good stuff and I think for an '86 show it is worth having. I would go 3.5 but since that is not an option I'll say 4.

Tight Set 1 I wasn't there, but I've enjoyed listening to this show; Jerry's thoughtful inflections on his guitar solos in Must've been Roses have indelibly scratched themselves into my mind.  The crowd "Not Fade Away" "We Want Phil" chant before Box is unfortunately not on this version.

I was there I remember crosby sitting in the grass outside so he would not violate his probation people swinging on the flag pole & a lot of people left during the 1st oncore but for the deadicated there was this feeling in the air that something special was going to happen this night Yes let phil sing let phil sing & the deadicated were rewarded with song    spacepiggio
Fire on fire Grow more & more impressed with 3 amp car system each and every time I pop this in. Woofers aren't only for rap Phil! Play this one back to back w/ 3/22/90 for a sample
